ican Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish: perhaps an Anglicized form of an unidentified Gaelic name. Compare   Merriman  .","English (Lancashire; of Norman origin) and French: nickname from Old French <i>marmion</i> ‘monkey, brat’."],"variants":[{"name":"Merriman","meanings":["English:","nickname from Middle English <i>mirie</i>, <i>merie</i>, <i>murie</i> ‘merry, pleasant’ + <i>man</i> ‘man’. Compare   Merry   1. This surname is established in Ireland (perhaps as an Anglicized form of an unidentified Gaelic name; compare   Marmion  ) as well as England.","there has probably been some confusion with <b>Marriman</b>, probably an occupational name meaning ‘servant of <i>Mary</i>’, from the female personal name <i>Mary</i> (see   Marie  ) + Middle English <i>man</i> in the sense ‘servant’, or perhaps a pet form of <i>Mary</i> using the hypocoristic suffix -<i>man</i>. The surname <i>Marriman</i> is now vanishingly rare in Britain and Ireland."]},{"name":"Marmon","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Gloucestershire):","variant of   Marmion  .","variant of <b>Marriman</b>, an occupational name meaning ‘servant of Mary’, from the female personal name <i>Mary</i> (see   Marie  ) + Middle English <i>man</i> in the sense ‘servant’."]}]},{"name":"Egidia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Greek <i>Aigidios</i>.  See  <b>Giles</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Egidia Marmion was born in 1183, in Kilpeck, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Marmion. She married Hugh de Kilpeck. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died in 1269, in her hometown, at the age of 86."},"et":{"1183–1269":"1183–1269","1160–1210":"1160–1210","1180–1244":"1180–1244","1213–1284":"1213–1284","1226–Female":"1226–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1226":"1226","1269":"1269","Abt 1213?":"umbes 1213","1213":"1213","about 1226":"umbes 1226","1244":"1244","1210":"1